"Now take your turns, ye Muses, to rehearse His friend’s complaints, and mighty magic verse. ¢ Bring running water ; bind those altars round With filiets, and with vervain strow the ground: Make fat with frankincense the sacred fires, “T'o re-inflame my Daphnis with desires. \"Tis done : we want but verse.— Restore, my charms, My lingering Daphnis to my longing armis."